                     <p>
                        <placeName/>

                        <persName xmlns:tite="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/tite/1.0">
                           <forename>Richard</forename> le <surname>Campioun</surname>
                        </persName> son of <persName xmlns:tite="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/tite/1.0">
                           <forename>Henry</forename> le  <surname>Campioun</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_108031">Weletone</placeName>
                        </persName>, quit-claims to <persName xmlns:tite="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/tite/1.0">
                           <forename>Thomas</forename> the <surname>tailor</surname>
                        </persName> of the same and <persName xmlns:tite="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/tite/1.0">
                           <forename>Cristiana</forename> his wife</persName> for a certain sum of money, his right in 3 acres of arable land and 3 roods of meadow in <placeName xmlns:tite="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/tite/1.0" key="place_108031">W<supplied>elton</supplied>
                        </placeName>, which they had by the gift and sale of the said Henry his father, viz. in the west field, ½ acre at <placeName xmlns:tite="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/tite/1.0" type="minor">Wayetnesfel</placeName> by the land late of <persName xmlns:tite="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/tite/1.0">
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Martyn</surname>
                        </persName>: 3 half acres lying together at <placeName xmlns:tite="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/tite/1.0" type="minor">Cockesmedeoverende</placeName> by the land late of <persName xmlns:tite="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/tite/1.0">
                           <forename>William</forename> 
                           <surname>Ace</surname>
                        </persName>, and in 2 roods lying together beneath Le ... Mor by the land of <persName xmlns:tite="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/tite/1.0">
                           <forename>William</forename> de <surname>Caldecote</surname>
                        </persName>; in the north field, ½ acre above <placeName xmlns:tite="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/tite/1.0" type="minor">Ferifurlong</placeName> by the land which <persName xmlns:tite="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/tite/1.0">
                           <forename>Robert</forename> le <surname>Noreys</surname>
                        </persName> held in villainage; and in the south field ½ acre of meadow in at <placeName xmlns:tite="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/tite/1.0" type="minor">Mathewether</placeName> by the meadow of <persName xmlns:tite="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/tite/1.0">
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Malory</surname>
                        </persName>; and in the east field, a rood of meadow in <placeName xmlns:tite="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/tite/1.0" type="minor">Overende</placeName>, by the meadow late of <persName xmlns:tite="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/tite/1.0">
                           <forename>William</forename> 
                           <surname>Hoycke</surname>
                        </persName>. Given at
<pb xmlns:tite="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/tite/1.0" n="121"/>
                        <placeName xmlns:tite="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/tite/1.0"
                                   type="date"
                                   key="place_108031">Weletone</placeName> ’in itinere justiciar’. 
   Witnesses: <persName xmlns:tite="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/tite/1.0">
                           <forename>John</forename> of <surname>Tewe</surname>
                        </persName>,
   <persName xmlns:tite="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/tite/1.0">
                           <forename>Thomas</forename> 
                           <surname>Martyn</surname>
                        </persName>, 
   <persName xmlns:tite="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/tite/1.0">
                           <forename>Henry</forename> the <surname>heir</surname>
                        </persName>, 
   <persName xmlns:tite="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/tite/1.0">
                           <forename>Richard</forename> in <surname>gardino</surname>
                        </persName>, 
   <persName xmlns:tite="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/tite/1.0">
                           <forename>Benedict</forename> of <surname>Drayton</surname> in <placeName role="person" key="place_108031">Weletone</placeName>
                        </persName>. 
   <origDate when="1330-03-18">
                           <supplied>18 March 1330.</supplied>
                        </origDate>
                     </p>
